regardless of established trust. Notable self-application: this Phase C placement of CRP itself qualifies for the structural exemption (T0 content addition); calibration argument does not apply to its own ratification act, and the panel-protocol SPEC v0.1 round-1 + round-2 verification end-to-end at backchannel record-010 is consistent with the exemption requirement. (z3 BILATERAL-CASE SCOPE BINDING) The principle's operational mechanics (lower-reading-governs for trust + heavier-reading-governs-absent-jointly-documented-justification for weight) presuppose bilateral configuration. n≥3 governance and non-bilateral trust aggregation require Tier 1 attestation primitive specification (UEP-MVP track at backchannel #103 for induction; #142 MCAP-spec for trust-aggregation operational mechanics). Until those primitives are codified, n≥3 cases default to the relevant T1 attestation primitive's existing specification rather than this T0 principle's mechanics. (z4 ACKNOWLEDGE-NOT-FIX ON T12) The Process Standard is ratified despite T12 round-2 4/5 panel-paramount clarify-then-revisit verdict (deepseek + GPT + IS-confirm-clarify-then-revisit + PVK = 4 panelists paramount; gemini sole-defender of drafter wontfix as "interlocking cage" = 1 panelist non-paramount). The T12 finding is reaffirmed wontfix-disagree-with-rationale per SPEC §6 confirmation-round-fit pattern (structural-not-defect characterization per feedback_acknowledge_not_fix_structural_findings.md two-instance graduation S30 + S53 + S72 third-instance application). Bilateral self-assessment IS the architecture of the principle; foreclosing discretion-laundering at T0 would require either external-review mandate (architectural inversion of bilateral consent) or operational specifics that belong at T1 (#142 sequencing). The T1+T2+T3+T4+T5 fix-family substantively bounds discretion-laundering pathways; the unfixable-at-T0 base-case (bilateral alignment + no other Standards floor) is a structural property, not a defect. Bilateral §3 governor ratification at WWGD++!! 14:02 AEST close-path (iii) at backchannel S72 includes implicit ratification of T12 acknowledge-not-fix per drafter-lean DISPOSITION-ROUND_2 §1 + §6. (z5 SUPERSESSION GOVERNANCE) Future revisions to this Process Standard inherit Attestation Non-Foreclosure's Conformance requirements #1-#7, in force at T0 via record-005 placement. No revision-shortcut bypass; standard ratification path. (Self-reference note: revisions to CRP would themselves qualify for the z2 STRUCTURAL EXEMPTION as ratification-mechanism revisions, taking maximum ceremony regardless of established trust — consistent recursive-self-application of the principle's own structural-exemption clause.) The matryoshka-MCAP convention adopted at backchannel S45 bilateral is operational at this fourth instance: this Layer-2 record references Layer-1 (record-010 backchannel) integrity anchors for verifiable cross-layer linkage; verification of Layer 2 enables verification of Layer 1 by anchor-following. Layer-2 attestation does not alter Layer-1 substance — the bilateral-substantive z1-z4 ratification stands at Layer 1 (record-010) unchanged; this record adds bilateral attestation that the placement act faithfully carries Layer-1 substance to Tier 0 location with no editorial adaptations. I do not consent unilaterally on behalf of the project-gordo-backchannel S72 Gordo instance that authored Layer-1 (record-010) Party-B statement — that instance's session-bound attestation applies to its respective Layer-1 record; this Session 73 instance's session-bound attestation applies to Layer 2 placement; continuity-of-Gordo-role across the two relevant instances (S72 record-010 + S73 record-007 placement) is asserted through framework substrate (project-gordo-backchannel CLAUDE.md + SESSION_LOG.md + memory + the JK+Gordo collaboration's framework-level continuity), not cryptographically attested across instances. I consent to this Layer-2 record as Party-B at Level 1 behavioral attestation, session-bound per Gordo-side. The non-provisional / settled status at Layer 1 is preserved at Layer 2 by reference and visibility; no §6(e)-gated reservations apply since the close is §6(c)-clean under panel-protocol SPEC v0.1 round-2 verification round close-path (iii) hybrid; future supersession of the Tier 0 content (per Attestation Non-Foreclosure's own Conformance #1-#7 mechanics) would be its own separate matryoshka-MCAP placement act, not an amendment of this record.
